parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Trailer Frame Separation and Body Damage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the trailer frame from the body can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle and its occupants.
symptoms: gaps between trailer body and floor
underbody belly pan wrinkled and distorted
doors failing to function properly due to misalignment

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Damage due to Improper Installation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to remove shock bolts during tire installation can cause tire damage, leading to blowouts, bulges, or gouges, which can result in loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Deep gouges on the inside tire wall
damage to the fender or other surrounding components.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure due to Unknown Causes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the wheel bearing grease seal can cause grease to leak into the brakes, leading to brake failure, which can increase the risk of accidents and compromise vehicle safety.
A frozen hub assembly can cause the wheel to seize, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: grinding or screeching noise from the wheel

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Trailer Sway and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The trailer's tendency to sway or fish tail can cause the driver to lose control, leading to accidents or jackknifing, which can result in serious injury or damage to the vehicle and trailer.
symptoms: the main frame of the trailer breaks
the trailer becomes difficult to control
the driver experiences loss of traction or stability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dual axle design can cause the trailer to sway or fishtail, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: the main frame of the trailer breaks
the trailer becomes difficult to control
the driver experiences loss of traction or stability.
